
Overview of noun hopper

The noun hopper has 5 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (1) hopper -- (funnel-shaped receptacle; contents pass by gravity into a receptacle below)
2. hopper -- (someone who hops; "at hopscotch, the best hoppers are the children")
3. hop-picker, hopper -- (a machine used for picking hops)
4. grasshopper, hopper -- (terrestrial plant-eating insect with hind legs adapted for leaping)
5. grounder, ground ball, groundball, hopper -- ((baseball) a hit that travels along the ground)
